
Overview of adv forever

The adv forever has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (14) everlastingly, eternally, forever, evermore -- (for a limitless time; "no one can live forever"; "brightly beams our Father's mercy from his lighthouse evermore"- P.P.Bliss)
2. (2) forever, forever and a day -- (for a very long or seemingly endless time; "she took forever to write the paper"; "we had to wait forever and a day")
3. (2) constantly, always, forever, perpetually, incessantly -- (without interruption; "the world is constantly changing")
